SIMPLE: mercenary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mercenary
<hw>Mer"ce*na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>mercenarie</ets>, F. <ets>mercenaire</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>mercenarius</ets>, fr. <ets>merces</ets> wages, reward. See
<er>Mercy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Acting for reward; serving for
pay; paid; hired; hireling; venal; <as>as, <ex>mercenary</ex>
soldiers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Moved primarily by
considerations of pay or profit; greedy of gain; sordid; selfish.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For God forbid I should my papers blot⟦br⟧
With <qex>mercenary</qex> lines, with servile pen.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Venal</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mercenary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mercenary
<hw>Mer"ce*na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Mercenaries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>One who is hired; a
hireling; especially, a soldier hired into foreign service.</def>
<rj><au>Milman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mercer</ent>⟦br⟧
